quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
47,12,"Allah shall admit those who believe and do righteous works to the Gardens beneath which rivers flow. As for the unbelievers, they enjoy the pleasures of this transient life and eat as cattle eat. {1} The Fire shall be their resort.",footnotes:1:That is
47,13,"(O Prophet), how many are the cities that had greater power than your city that drove you out? We destroyed them and there was none to protect them. {1}",footnotes:1:The Prophet (peace be upon him) was sorely distressed on leaving Makkah. When he was compelled to emigrate
47,14,"Then, can he, who is on a Clear Guidance from His Lord, be like him whose evil deeds have been embellished to him, and who pursued their lusts? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
47,15,"Here is the parable of Paradise which the God-fearing have been promised: in it shall be rivers of incorruptible water, {1} rivers of milk unchanging in taste, {2} and rivers of wine, a delight to those that drink; {3} and rivers of pure honey. {4} In it they will have every kind of fruit as well as forgiveness from their Lord. {5} Can such be like those who will abide in the Fire and will be given a boiling water to drink that will tear their bowels apart?",footnotes:1:Literally
47,16,"Among them some give ear to you. But no sooner do they leave your presence than they ask those endowed with knowledge: “What is it that he said just now?” {1} Such are those whose hearts Allah has sealed and who pursue their lusts. {2}",footnotes:1:This is concerning those disbelievers and hypocrites and unbelieving followers of the former Books
47,17,"As for those who were led to the Guidance, {1} Allah increases them in their guidance and causes them to grow in God-fearing. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
47,18,"Are they waiting, then, for anything else than the Last Hour to suddenly come upon them? {1} Already some of its tokens have come. {2} But when it does actually come upon them, where will any time be left for them to take heed?",footnotes:1:That is
47,19,"Know, therefore, (O Prophet), that there is no god but Allah, and ask forgiveness for your shortcomings and also for (the shortcomings of) believing men and believing women. {1} Allah knows the places where you move about and where you dwell.",footnotes:1:One of the morals taught to man by Islam is also this: However hard and sincerely may man be trying to serve and worship his Lord and fighting and struggling in the cause of His Religion
